originalText.text: Assistant Manager, Jean Pierre, is a gentleman with kind manners, and he’s very helpful. I had a flat tire. When Tesla service came to replace it he helped move my car to a perfect location for the repair. I’m grateful for his good service at 507 West 21st St. in NYC.

originalText.text:
Great Customer Service!!!!!!!
I’ve parked at the Edison ParkFast on W.21st right off of 10th Ave for almost a year. The service has always been nothing short of great. The team of attendants are awesome, professional, and polite and always a pleasure to interact with them.
Guyto is the nicest and most helpful person, I see him almost every day and him being the 1st person I encounter almost every morning starts my day off on a positive note and sets the tone for my day .
Boaz the manager of this location as well as the location on 10th Ave and 20th St is awesome, I encountered a small issue and Boaz went above and beyond in ensuring that I was satisfied, the service he provided me with as well as the resolution to the problem is a type of service that one no longer sees when parking at other parking franchises.
If you want your vehicle to be treated with care and know it will be safe I definitely suggest you give them a try.

originalText.text: At this parking spot after we used an online company to secure parking we were charged extra. We didn't realize it initially, but the time stamp on our parking ticket was wrong. It time stamped us parking our vehicle a whole hour prior to the actual time we showed up, which resulted in us being charged extra. Someone else ahead of us had the same issue...seems like a scam to me or their system time is off and they haven't realized it.
